57.4	McGill_University	McGill University	McGill University is a public research university located in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. The university bears the name of James McGill, a prominent Montreal merchant from Glasgow, Scotland and alumnus of Glasgow University, whose bequest formed the beginning of the university. Founded in 1821, McGill was chartered during the British colonial era, 46 years before the Canadian Confederation, making it one of the oldest universities in Canada.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/29/McGill_University_CoA.svg/160px-McGill_University_CoA.svg.png
